(James sighs)

05:08.369 --> 05:11.673
(light dramatic music)

05:26.617 --> 05:30.322
(bottles thudding)

05:30.357 --> 05:33.255
(alcohol sloshing)

05:38.233 --> 05:41.197
(guzzling alcohol)

05:44.712 --> 05:47.269
(light music)

05:57.417 --> 06:00.849
(bottle clatters)

06:00.884 --> 06:02.988
- I feel like I failed my wife.

06:05.361 --> 06:06.959
I feel like I failed my kids.

06:09.370 --> 06:13.469
I kept telling myself that
I didn't have a problem,

06:13.504 --> 06:16.700
but when I woke up
in my daughter's room

06:16.735 --> 06:19.334
with holes punched in her walls,

06:21.678 --> 06:24.009
that's when I finally
realized how deep I was.

06:25.281 --> 06:26.617
It didn't matter though.

06:27.686 --> 06:30.389
My wife already packed the car
two hours before I woke up.

06:37.123 --> 06:41.400
I don't even know where
they are anymore. (cries)

06:48.238 --> 06:51.035
- Thanks for sharing.

06:51.071 --> 06:54.842
I mean, that's what the
bottle does to us, right?

06:57.247 --> 06:58.549
It makes you a liar.

07:01.478 --> 07:06.249
You become your worst self and
worst version of ourselves.

07:09.295 --> 07:11.859
That's the hardest
part, I think,

07:14.232 --> 07:15.731
admitting what you've become.

07:17.669 --> 07:22.199
I know it took me a long,
long time to admit that.

07:23.302 --> 07:27.479
I know that if it wasn't for
this group and, and my, my son,

07:30.944 --> 07:32.580
I'd be at the bottom
of a glass somewhere.

07:32.615 --> 07:36.312
That's, that's without
question, so...

07:40.960 --> 07:43.825
(chairs rustling)

07:50.100 --> 07:51.762
- Hey, um...

07:51.797 --> 07:54.666
Sorry for losing it back there.

07:54.701 --> 07:55.938
Not a good first impression.

07:55.974 --> 07:57.306
- Please.

07:57.341 --> 07:59.506
My first meeting I was rocking

07:59.541 --> 08:01.271
in a fetal position for hours.

08:02.212 --> 08:03.108
It gets better.

08:04.182 --> 08:06.914
(truck horn beeping)

08:08.646 --> 08:09.521
That's me.

08:11.551 --> 08:13.285
Keep coming back.

08:13.320 --> 08:14.119
- Okay.

08:18.227 --> 08:20.697
(horn honks)

08:27.302 --> 08:28.301
- Come on.

08:28.337 --> 08:30.537
- Settle down.

08:30.572 --> 08:32.102
Just making sure you heard me.

08:32.137 --> 08:34.041
You know how old
people's hearing is, huh?

08:34.076 --> 08:37.041
- Well I'll tell you what,
maybe if you keep smarting off,

08:37.077 --> 08:38.847
the horn won't be the
only thing screaming.

08:38.882 --> 08:41.553
- Okay, settle down or you're
not getting your lunch.

08:43.220 --> 08:44.349
- Go, go, go.

08:44.385 --> 08:45.617
Let's go.

08:45.652 --> 08:48.956
(upbeat country music)

08:57.096 --> 09:00.138
So, uh, what's on
Sarah's menu today?

09:00.173 --> 09:01.564
- Peanut butter and pickles.

09:01.599 --> 09:02.998
- Ooh.

09:03.501 --> 09:05.509
How much longer you gonna
be able to stay on this diet?

09:05.544 --> 09:07.546
- Honestly, it's not
as bad as you think.

09:08.839 --> 09:10.542
- Yeah, it is.

09:10.577 --> 09:13.376
(engine rumbling)

09:17.687 --> 09:19.755
- Look, you can judge
me all you want,

09:19.791 --> 09:24.725
but all the books say that
the more we do together,

09:24.761 --> 09:27.021
the more it's like
we're both pregnant.

09:27.056 --> 09:29.167
- Ha!
- Which, it's

09:29.202 --> 09:30.602
it's a good thing, I think.

09:32.370 --> 09:33.902
Speaking of which, actually,

09:35.269 --> 09:37.906
Sarah said she didn't get
your RSVP for the baby shower.

09:39.212 --> 09:42.371
Sent them out a week ago.

09:42.407 --> 09:44.842
I, I told her they
probably got lost in the mail.

09:44.877 --> 09:48.411
So, did it get lost in the mail?

09:50.320 --> 09:52.448
- I don't know.

09:53.721 --> 09:56.254
- Dad, is everything okay?

09:58.062 --> 09:59.197
- Yeah.

09:59.232 --> 10:04.201
(upbeat country music continues)

10:04.236 --> 10:06.595
- No, I, I know, I know.

10:07.298 --> 10:09.366
I was thinking about
her last night too.

10:11.310 --> 10:12.941
- Sarah would go over baby names

10:14.412 --> 10:17.009
and this one's gonna be a boy,

10:17.045 --> 10:19.140
but she really wants the
next one to be a girl.

10:19.176 --> 10:22.918
So you throw out
the name Trisha,

10:24.347 --> 10:26.152
that's a possibility
down the line.

10:28.354 --> 10:32.587
And I dunno, I wasn't
sure how you'd take that.

10:35.665 --> 10:37.893
(woman laughs)
(ominous music)

10:37.929 --> 10:40.969
(suspenseful music)

10:42.173 --> 10:43.004
- Good name.

10:48.541 --> 10:49.439
- Yeah.

10:52.982 --> 10:57.185
Well, hey, six years
sober today, big guy. Huh?

10:57.220 --> 10:59.114
Come on.

10:59.149 --> 11:01.324
She'd be proud of you, Dad.

11:01.359 --> 11:04.828
(upbeat music continues)

11:19.913 --> 11:22.340
- 59326.

11:24.346 --> 11:25.211
- Yep.

11:26.920 --> 11:28.944
- 57291.

11:28.979 --> 11:31.613
(cases clattering)

11:36.653 --> 11:39.396
- You do know how long
your route is today, right?

11:39.431 --> 11:42.125
You guys are doing the dead 10

11:42.161 --> 11:44.560
and you're already
late. As always.

11:47.841 --> 11:50.307
Tell me, you really need to
review all this stuff again?

11:50.342 --> 11:52.138
- It's protocol, Frank.

11:52.174 --> 11:54.204
- Protocol is to get
this shit back in the truck

11:54.240 --> 11:56.638
so I can get back to
my clients, James.

12:01.783 --> 12:04.349
- In a better mood than usual.

12:05.288 --> 12:07.055
- 20248.

12:08.117 --> 12:11.092
(cases clattering)

12:13.967 --> 12:17.065
49826.

12:17.797 --> 12:18.693
- [Casey] Got it.

12:27.213 --> 12:29.445
(metal rattling)

12:29.480 --> 12:30.672
- Pull that.
- Yeah.

12:42.153 --> 12:43.520
- Fucking hot box in here.

12:44.954 --> 12:45.863
Shit.

12:47.732 --> 12:49.592
It's not even noon
and it's this hot.

12:51.798 --> 12:52.903
This thing work?

12:55.165 --> 12:56.808
(tapping thermometer)

12:58.805 --> 13:00.108
(Casey exhales)

13:02.346 --> 13:03.876
Oh my god.

13:03.911 --> 13:05.448
The hell's that guy hauling?

13:05.483 --> 13:07.814
- It's not our business.

13:07.849 --> 13:10.283
- All right.
(cases thudding)

13:14.085 --> 13:15.456
I got it, I got it.

13:15.492 --> 13:17.087
(Casey grunts)

13:17.122 --> 13:18.922
(case thuds)
- You okay?

13:18.957 --> 13:20.622
- [Casey] Oh fuck.

13:20.658 --> 13:21.629
- [James] You all right?
- No, no, no, no, no, no.

13:21.664 --> 13:24.601
I dropped a fucking pen.

13:24.637 --> 13:25.565
Fuck.
- What do you mean a pen?

13:25.601 --> 13:27.565
- A pen light.

13:27.600 --> 13:29.841
Sarah gave me this light with
my name on it specifically

13:29.876 --> 13:32.503
'cause I'm always losing
shit in this fucking truck.

13:34.543 --> 13:35.838
- Let's go.

13:35.873 --> 13:37.105
Come on.

13:37.141 --> 13:40.251
- (groans) Fuck it.

13:40.286 --> 13:41.614
Fuck it, let's go.

13:41.650 --> 13:43.019
Okay, it's fine.

13:46.285 --> 13:50.153
- Look, I don't know
what's in there,

13:50.188 --> 13:51.519
but if we break it, we buy it.

13:51.554 --> 13:52.560
- I got it.
- You understand that?

13:52.595 --> 13:55.262
- Yeah, I got it.

13:55.298 --> 13:57.196
- Look, can you just don't
tell Sarah about this, okay

13:57.231 --> 13:59.304
'cause then she's gonna
start worrying about

13:59.339 --> 14:00.804
me losing my gun next

14:00.839 --> 14:03.641
and it's gonna turn
into a whole thing.

14:03.676 --> 14:05.876
- What, what is the
real issue here?

14:05.912 --> 14:08.170
- There's no issue, I just
don't want her to stress

14:08.205 --> 14:09.136
until the baby comes.

14:09.172 --> 14:10.548
- About a pen?

14:10.584 --> 14:12.273
- Yeah, it's gonna
stress her out.

14:12.309 --> 14:14.017
- Little words of wisdom.

14:14.052 --> 14:16.377
Your stress starts when
that baby pops its head out.

14:16.413 --> 14:18.956
You got that?
- Dad, please.

14:21.226 --> 14:23.685
- Fine.

14:23.721 --> 14:27.564
I will not tell Sarah
that you lost a pen light

14:27.599 --> 14:29.197
with your little initials on it.

14:32.669 --> 14:35.367
(door thuds)
- Yeah.

14:35.403 --> 14:37.904
Nothing more stress free
than driving a cash truck

14:37.939 --> 14:39.977
10 miles to
bumfuck nowhere.

14:41.747 --> 14:44.575
Beautiful, beautiful
bumfuck nowhere.

14:45.681 --> 14:48.480
(birds chirping)

14:51.258 --> 14:53.991
(ominous music)

14:59.424 --> 15:03.264
(door thuds)
(upbeat rock music)

15:09.542 --> 15:14.572
(upbeat rock music continues)

15:23.280 --> 15:25.088
- Dad? You all right?

15:26.258 --> 15:27.123
- Yeah.

15:31.221 --> 15:34.356
(truck rattling)

15:34.391 --> 15:37.263
- Fucking truck's falling apart.

15:37.298 --> 15:39.768
- It's got a little
bit of character to it.

15:39.803 --> 15:43.407
(upbeat rock music continues)

15:43.442 --> 15:45.273
(engine rumbling)

15:52.343 --> 15:53.479
(upbeat rock music continues)

16:02.286 --> 16:05.227
(indistinct chatter)

16:06.793 --> 16:07.658
- Hey.

16:10.594 --> 16:12.432
Am I gonna have
to twist your arm

16:12.467 --> 16:14.236
or are you gonna finally
come over for dinner tonight?

16:16.802 --> 16:20.407
- I, uh, I have to host a
meeting tonight, I'm sorry.

16:23.273 --> 16:26.282
(light music)

16:26.317 --> 16:29.778
- You know you have an actual
family outside that circle?

16:29.813 --> 16:31.852
- Yeah, but not one
that's gonna drive a truck

16:31.887 --> 16:33.321
through the living room.

16:34.625 --> 16:35.620
- Not yet anyways.

16:37.821 --> 16:41.158
All right, look, the
offer still stands. Okay?

16:41.193 --> 16:42.966
Just come over whenever.

16:43.001 --> 16:46.330
Just thought it'd be
a good idea for you to

16:46.366 --> 16:48.671
get away from your
vices for a bit.

16:48.706 --> 16:50.835
(light music continues)

16:50.870 --> 16:51.768
- Case.

16:59.179 --> 17:01.646
You want me to bring a pie or...

17:04.381 --> 17:07.784
(light music continues)

17:13.862 --> 17:16.826
(heavy rock music)

17:23.434 --> 17:24.801
(heavy rock music continues)

17:32.784 --> 17:36.549
(heavy rock music continues)

17:47.460 --> 17:49.497
- Careful with the C4?
- Man, I, I know

17:49.532 --> 17:52.361
it's unstable as fuck, man.
- Well, everything's unstable.

17:52.396 --> 17:53.665
- Speak for yourself.

18:01.910 --> 18:04.610
(phone ringing)

18:06.817 --> 18:08.545
- Yeah, you're late.

18:08.581 --> 18:10.517
No, we're ready. Are
you fucking ready?

18:11.984 --> 18:12.882
Right.

18:14.086 --> 18:15.286
Let's do it.

18:15.321 --> 18:19.523
(heavy rock music continues)

18:19.558 --> 18:24.159
(crickets chirping)
(light music)

18:24.662 --> 18:26.297
- Hey, except that it's the
truth.

18:26.332 --> 18:27.572
- No, it's not. No it's not.

18:27.607 --> 18:28.833
- Uh, it's the truth.

18:29.469 --> 18:31.775
First day, little
Case on the job,

18:31.811 --> 18:34.811
a little baby in
his Kevlar vest.

18:34.846 --> 18:36.704
Got his baby, new little id,

18:36.740 --> 18:38.815
it's right off the
press still hot,

18:38.850 --> 18:40.551
carrying his first bag of money.

18:40.586 --> 18:42.118
Big bag of money.

18:42.154 --> 18:46.982
He's so nervous, he's, I
would say raining sweat.

18:47.994 --> 18:49.653
- He's exaggerating.
- You left a trail

18:49.689 --> 18:53.158
on the sidewalk, there's
no question about this.

18:53.194 --> 18:56.727
Anyway, back to the truth.

18:56.763 --> 19:01.172
All jittery, like, somebody
comes up beside him

19:01.207 --> 19:05.439
and taps him on the shoulder
just to ask the time.

19:05.475 --> 19:10.978
He whips around like Dirty
Harry right in the face

19:11.013 --> 19:12.913
of 147-year-old woman.

19:12.948 --> 19:14.081
- Okay, calm down.

19:14.116 --> 19:16.014
She was probably in her fifties.

19:16.049 --> 19:17.915
- Maybe 128.

19:17.950 --> 19:20.989
- And I'm regretting inviting
you to this dinner already.

19:21.024 --> 19:23.920
- Oh, ah. I'm glad you did.

19:25.127 --> 19:26.524
I needed a homecooked meal.

19:26.559 --> 19:28.122
- Yep, and I needed
a good laugh.

19:30.994 --> 19:35.932
Well, cheers to 30 days
on the job as a team.

19:37.334 --> 19:38.433
- Cheers.

19:38.468 --> 19:40.673
(glasses clinking)

19:44.146 --> 19:45.709
- So how was the route today?

19:45.744 --> 19:47.380
Any old lady try and
knock over the truck?

19:47.415 --> 19:50.612
- Okay, very funny,
baby. Thank you.

19:50.647 --> 19:53.152
No, no old ladies. No nothing.

19:53.188 --> 19:55.688
Just, just nice and quiet.

19:57.525 --> 19:59.494
- That's how me and
the little guy like it.

20:00.831 --> 20:02.395
- I, I don't know.

20:02.431 --> 20:05.133
I, I'd kill for some
action, honestly.

20:05.169 --> 20:08.501
I mean, just one
tweaker with a gun

20:08.537 --> 20:12.067
so I have an excuse to
pull my taser at least.

20:15.205 --> 20:20.218
- You are gonna find that
the best action is no action.

20:21.511 --> 20:22.880
Trust me on that.

20:27.353 --> 20:32.395
(light music continues)

20:45.939 --> 20:49.443
- Jeremy really let out the
waterworks this time, huh?

20:49.478 --> 20:50.838
- First week's the
hardest, you know that.

20:50.874 --> 20:53.708
- Yeah, you know
more than anyone.

20:53.743 --> 20:55.350
Hey, you hang in there, brother.

20:55.386 --> 20:57.246
Another year clear is
another year to stumble.

20:57.281 --> 20:58.080
- Right.

20:59.791 --> 21:00.687
Thanks, Pete.

21:04.554 --> 21:07.430
(engine rumbling)

21:14.437 --> 21:16.301
- Hey, looks like you're
moving slow today.

21:16.336 --> 21:18.070
Frank's gonna be pissed.

21:18.105 --> 21:19.533
- Always is.

21:19.569 --> 21:22.104
(light music)

21:23.473 --> 21:25.707
(door thuds)

21:25.742 --> 21:30.252
So what's on the menu today?

21:30.288 --> 21:32.580
- Turkey and fluff.
(engine rumbling)

21:32.615 --> 21:35.491
(light rock music)

21:57.211 --> 22:02.276
(muffled talking)

22:07.189 --> 22:08.919
- You're late again.

22:08.955 --> 22:10.488
I needed these things
outta here 10 minutes ago.

22:10.523 --> 22:12.256
- There was traffic, Frank.

22:12.291 --> 22:13.925
- I'll bet.

22:13.960 --> 22:15.661
Come on, Brody, I don't
have time for these excuses.

22:15.697 --> 22:17.792
I have a bank full of
people waiting for me.

22:17.827 --> 22:20.134
- Why are there four cases?

22:20.169 --> 22:21.935
Only says three here.

22:21.970 --> 22:22.769
- What?

22:24.711 --> 22:26.007
Why do you care?

22:26.043 --> 22:28.773
Just haul the stuff.

22:28.808 --> 22:30.679
- There are rules
and protocols, Frank,

22:30.714 --> 22:34.445
and this clipboard doesn't
say anything about this case.

22:34.480 --> 22:36.176
- The clipboard, yeah?

22:36.211 --> 22:37.815
What does it say about
me calling your boss

22:37.850 --> 22:39.156
and telling him you're
coming late to work

22:39.191 --> 22:42.292
because you're going
to AA meetings?

22:42.328 --> 22:43.455
Maybe he doesn't know
that you were kicked off

22:43.490 --> 22:45.394
the force for being a drunk.

22:45.429 --> 22:46.821
Listen, Brody, I hate
to break it to you,

22:46.856 --> 22:48.196
but you're not a cop anymore.

22:48.231 --> 22:50.461
You're a mailman with a gun.

22:50.496 --> 22:51.666
Just deliver the mail.

22:54.070 --> 22:56.638
(light music)

23:06.885 --> 23:08.485
(pen scratching)

23:17.422 --> 23:19.892
(case thuds)

23:22.462 --> 23:26.496
(upbeat country music)

23:26.531 --> 23:29.330
(engine rumbling)

23:37.312 --> 23:39.450
