47:12.628 --> 47:14.994
but this is fucking crazy.

47:15.029 --> 47:18.329
- Let's just get you
back to Sarah now, okay?

47:19.528 --> 47:21.530
We gotta clean that
out, it's festering.

47:24.306 --> 47:25.171
- Here.

47:26.168 --> 47:27.676
- No, it's an infection,

47:27.712 --> 47:29.538
we have to take care
of that infection.

47:32.043 --> 47:33.608
We're gonna need some alcohol.

47:35.719 --> 47:37.380
- I don't mean to
tempt you, Dad,

47:37.415 --> 47:39.119
but I would kill for
some moonshine right now.

47:41.084 --> 47:42.287
- What about vodka?

47:44.060 --> 47:46.521
- That would work too,
but I don't think there's

47:46.556 --> 47:48.461
gonna be any vodka in here.
- I got a thermos

47:48.497 --> 47:49.459
full of vodka.

47:54.932 --> 47:57.731
(birds chirping)

48:00.005 --> 48:01.201
- It's gonna be all right.

48:01.236 --> 48:02.340
Calm down, all right?

48:04.205 --> 48:05.079
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

48:07.450 --> 48:08.346
- [Smoke]<i> Sure</i> .

48:11.553 --> 48:12.713
- Fucking lunatic.

48:15.416 --> 48:18.994
(birds continue chirping)

48:22.392 --> 48:25.429
- Dad, you've been
drinking again.

48:29.300 --> 48:33.272
- I never, I never
really stopped.

48:35.740 --> 48:36.605
I...

48:39.143 --> 48:43.117
I tried, I, I did, I just...

48:46.153 --> 48:47.923
You know, I filled
that thermos every day,

48:47.959 --> 48:50.850
and I'd go tell addicts
to keep clean and I was...

48:52.930 --> 48:55.690
- All this time you've
just been lying to me?

48:57.635 --> 49:00.059
(James sighs)
(light music)

49:00.095 --> 49:02.466
- I tried.

49:02.501 --> 49:04.463
Your mother and I just, you,
you wouldn't understand.

49:04.498 --> 49:07.070
- Don't say that, don't say...

49:07.105 --> 49:08.637
I remember more than you know.

49:10.977 --> 49:16.051
(woman singing with guitar)

49:27.094 --> 49:31.594
(woman singing with guitar
continues)

49:34.935 --> 49:37.072
- This is so humiliating.

49:38.000 --> 49:39.605
- What?

49:39.640 --> 49:41.306
Kidding me?

49:41.342 --> 49:43.436
These people, they'd give
the right arm to be able

49:43.471 --> 49:45.146
to camp next to a gator's nest.

49:47.045 --> 49:48.484
Your left ankle.
- Oh.

49:48.519 --> 49:50.914
- Your elbow.
- Elbow.

49:50.950 --> 49:52.244
- [James] Your wife.

49:52.280 --> 49:56.320
- Hey! (laughs)

49:56.356 --> 49:59.627
Well, most people aren't
stuffed in a cop car.

49:59.662 --> 50:01.156
We look like criminals.

50:01.191 --> 50:03.194
- I think this is sweet.

50:03.230 --> 50:05.364
I think I'm riding
shotgun into a raid.

50:06.569 --> 50:07.828
- My man Case.

50:10.003 --> 50:12.002
See? Respects the old man's job.

50:12.038 --> 50:13.201
Somebody does in this car.

50:13.237 --> 50:14.635
- Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah.

50:14.670 --> 50:18.377
- Mother has a total
disrespect for the law.

50:22.811 --> 50:24.851
- [Trisha]<i> Oh, it's</i>
<i> dark as pitch out there.</i>

50:24.886 --> 50:26.851
- It is, there's no lights.

50:26.886 --> 50:29.685
(engine rumbling)

50:32.496 --> 50:34.855
(tires screeching)

50:36.400 --> 50:37.990
That maniac.

50:38.997 --> 50:40.327
- You're off duty.

50:40.363 --> 50:41.736
- They can kill somebody.

50:41.772 --> 50:43.968
- Dad, come on.
- Look at him.

50:44.004 --> 50:45.933
- Okay, you are off duty.

50:46.736 --> 50:48.677
- I gotta talk to him,
he's gotta slow down.

50:48.712 --> 50:51.847
(sirens wailing)
It's okay.

50:51.882 --> 50:54.473
- Babe.
- Two minutes, come on now.

50:54.509 --> 50:57.977
(sirens continue wailing)

51:01.052 --> 51:02.355
Hand me my gun?

51:03.758 --> 51:04.819
Please.
- No.

51:07.258 --> 51:09.021
(glove compartment thuds)

51:10.802 --> 51:14.163
Seriously?
- He can hurt somebody.

51:14.199 --> 51:17.667
(sirens continue wailing)

51:24.208 --> 51:26.275
(suspenseful music)

51:26.310 --> 51:30.009
All right, stay in the car.

51:35.723 --> 51:37.889
(door thuds)

51:37.925 --> 51:41.691
(suspenseful music)

51:45.626 --> 51:47.769
License and registration.

51:47.804 --> 51:49.600
- You don't look like a cop.

51:55.570 --> 51:58.272
- License and registration, kid.

51:58.308 --> 52:01.381
(crickets chirping)

52:04.253 --> 52:07.219
You're going 100 in a
50, you aware of that?

52:07.254 --> 52:08.456
- Yes sir. It
won't happen again.

52:08.491 --> 52:09.915
- Yeah?

52:09.950 --> 52:11.653
See, I was in a good
mood because I'm taking

52:11.689 --> 52:13.420
my family camping and
then I got in a bad mood

52:13.456 --> 52:15.423
when you rocketed past us.

52:15.459 --> 52:17.427
I wanna get in a
good mood again.

52:17.462 --> 52:20.830
So, Mr. Corey
Marshon, if I find out

52:20.865 --> 52:23.599
that you're going two miles
over the speed limit anywhere

52:23.634 --> 52:25.432
in this county, I'm
taking you to jail.

52:25.467 --> 52:27.072
Do you understand that?

52:27.107 --> 52:29.842
- Yes, sir.
- Slow down.

52:29.878 --> 52:32.841
(crickets chirping)

52:39.821 --> 52:42.686
(engine rumbling)

52:46.057 --> 52:48.527
(door thuds)

52:52.867 --> 52:53.994
We're on the move.

52:57.738 --> 52:59.632
What?

52:59.667 --> 53:01.074
- You said you wouldn't do this.

53:01.110 --> 53:02.971
- It was a little
stop, it's over.

53:03.006 --> 53:06.108
He was driving a hundred miles
an hour, he'd kill somebody.

53:06.144 --> 53:07.612
- Dad, really?

53:12.655 --> 53:13.519
- All right.

53:15.022 --> 53:18.154
No more cop, I promise.

53:18.190 --> 53:21.153
(crickets chirping)

53:23.566 --> 53:24.464
Sorry.

53:28.362 --> 53:29.862
Sorry.

53:29.897 --> 53:31.801
(truck horn blares)
(car crashing)

53:37.773 --> 53:41.413
(sirens wailing)
(muffled talking)

53:41.448 --> 53:43.817
- [Dispatch]<i> Yes,</i>
<i> engine five is arriving.</i>

53:43.853 --> 53:46.882
(suspenseful music)

53:49.753 --> 53:52.661
<i> Dispatch requesting</i>
<i> medvac at scene.</i>

53:53.097 --> 53:58.157
(sirens continue wailing)
(somber music)

54:11.276 --> 54:13.074
- Sir, are you okay?

54:13.110 --> 54:14.543
Sir?

54:14.579 --> 54:15.416
Guys, I need you
to come down here.

54:17.546 --> 54:20.113
Ma'am, can you hear me?

54:23.718 --> 54:27.692
(muffled police radio chatter)

54:29.097 --> 54:32.631
(sirens continue wailing)

54:33.804 --> 54:37.273
(somber music continues)

54:49.979 --> 54:51.281
-[Firefighter 2]<i> You go on the</i>
<i> other side.</i>

54:51.750 --> 54:53.481
-[Firefighter 1]<i> Ma'am, are you</i>
<i> all right</i> ?

54:53.516 --> 54:56.985
(somber music continues)

55:01.964 --> 55:05.158
(helicopter whirring)

55:11.467 --> 55:12.671
- I hated you.

55:14.372 --> 55:16.672
I wished it was you.

55:16.707 --> 55:18.944
I wished it was
you instead of her.

55:18.980 --> 55:20.349
I was so angry.

55:21.551 --> 55:24.012
I must've went through 15
pillows I punched 'em so hard.

55:26.021 --> 55:27.785
And we told you, Dad.

55:29.952 --> 55:33.019
We told you not to
stop, just keep driving,

55:33.054 --> 55:38.131
but you just had to
turn on those lights.

55:38.167 --> 55:39.764
Just had to turn
on those lights.

55:43.702 --> 55:45.803
But you didn't drive
that truck into Mom.

55:47.904 --> 55:51.279
And you need to stop
punishing yourself

55:51.314 --> 55:53.448
for something that you
had no control over.

55:55.182 --> 55:56.352
She wouldn't want that.

55:59.682 --> 56:05.285
I think it's just, it hurts,

56:05.320 --> 56:10.025
it hurts to admit she's gone
because of a stupid accident.

56:14.095 --> 56:17.497
- We gotta move and
we gotta this thermos.

56:17.533 --> 56:20.203
(tense music)

56:20.239 --> 56:22.972
(drill whirring)

56:28.545 --> 56:31.915
(tense music continues)

56:35.190 --> 56:40.562
(drill continues whirring)

56:40.597 --> 56:43.663
Just gotta find something we
can get through that latch.

56:46.102 --> 56:49.735
(drill continues whirring)

56:55.736 --> 56:58.370
(metal clinks)

57:05.087 --> 57:08.457
(tense music continues)

57:23.106 --> 57:26.739
(drill continues whirring)

57:38.284 --> 57:41.083
(metal clatters)

57:44.026 --> 57:46.088
(James grunts)

57:52.033 --> 57:53.297
Over there.

57:53.333 --> 57:54.896
No, turn your head.

57:54.931 --> 57:57.264
There's still gas
in that, get back.

58:01.936 --> 58:05.580
(drill continues whirring)

58:09.480 --> 58:12.279
(metal clinking)

58:13.649 --> 58:15.689
(metal clatters)

58:20.227 --> 58:21.123
-[Rook] Okay.

58:25.463 --> 58:26.667
Keep it going.

58:30.974 --> 58:33.773
(metal clinking)

58:48.156 --> 58:50.790
(James groans)

59:02.170 --> 59:04.969
- More. More.

59:08.374 --> 59:11.008
(Casey groans)

59:14.952 --> 59:17.586
(Casey grunts)

59:19.517 --> 59:21.051
- Okay, all right.

59:28.064 --> 59:30.192
(metal clattering)

59:32.466 --> 59:34.669
- That does not look good.

59:42.641 --> 59:46.274
(drill continues whirring)

59:51.113 --> 59:53.787
- [Smoke]<i> This is taking</i>
<i> forever.</i>

59:59.086 --> 01:00:01.553
- I don't think he's bluffing.

01:00:03.832 --> 01:00:06.393
Those doors look like
they're about to pop already.

01:00:08.997 --> 01:00:11.239
- How many bullets you got?

01:00:11.274 --> 01:00:12.240
- Dropped my gun on the bridge,

01:00:12.275 --> 01:00:14.139
all I got left is a bug zapper.

01:00:14.174 --> 01:00:15.204
Here.

01:00:17.940 --> 01:00:21.111
(drill continues whirring)

01:00:25.682 --> 01:00:28.217
(sparks zapping)

01:00:31.121 --> 01:00:32.860
- We can make these
tasers work I think,

01:00:33.196 --> 01:00:34.456
then we cut it to two.

01:00:35.092 --> 01:00:37.463
- Yeah, yeah, just
two heavily armed pros

01:00:37.498 --> 01:00:39.060
with armor-piercing bullets.

01:00:39.429 --> 01:00:41.736
I'm sure our bare hands are
more than enough against that.

01:00:43.107 --> 01:00:43.971
What are you doing?

01:00:44.474 --> 01:00:47.335
- Unless...
(light dramatic music)

01:00:51.042 --> 01:00:53.946
We got a lighter and
some high-proof alcohol.

01:00:55.482 --> 01:00:57.316
Let's even the odds.

01:00:58.052 --> 01:01:01.685
- Dad, a Molotov in this tight
space, I mean, it's suicide.

01:01:01.720 --> 01:01:03.348
My leg's covered in that stuff.

01:01:03.384 --> 01:01:05.287
One little mistake
and we'll all go up.

01:01:08.826 --> 01:01:10.930
- Now let's get some air.

01:01:11.893 --> 01:01:14.461
(tense music)

01:01:22.640 --> 01:01:23.672
Can you make it?

01:01:23.707 --> 01:01:25.309
- Yeah.
- Okay.

01:01:25.344 --> 01:01:26.143
Come on.

01:01:27.084 --> 01:01:28.849
(Casey groans)

01:01:33.653 --> 01:01:35.647
- She's gonna crack any second!

01:01:36.887 --> 01:01:39.189
(drill continues whirring)

01:01:41.561 --> 01:01:44.964
(tense music continues)

01:01:52.905 --> 01:01:54.471
[Smoke] It's gonna crack any
second!

01:01:54.507 --> 01:01:56.043
- Stop! Stop!

01:01:56.078 --> 01:01:56.877
Please!

01:01:58.781 --> 01:02:00.840
[Casey] Please stop, I can't
take this anymore!

01:02:00.876 --> 01:02:01.750
- [Rook] Cut it.

01:02:03.516 --> 01:02:04.412
What'd you say?

01:02:06.413 --> 01:02:07.855
- [Casey] I can't take it
anymore.

01:02:09.622 --> 01:02:11.925
I'll come out, okay?

01:02:12.525 --> 01:02:13.586
I'll come out.

01:02:15.860 --> 01:02:17.660
I need to get to a hospital.

01:02:18.095 --> 01:02:20.098
Just take me to a
hospital, please.

01:02:21.468 --> 01:02:23.431
(metal screeches)

01:02:24.134 --> 01:02:26.633
- [Smoke] The
kid's doing an act.

01:02:27.035 --> 01:02:29.668
- [Casey]<i> Please, stop.</i>

01:02:35.043 --> 01:02:38.083
(suspenseful music)

01:02:42.283 --> 01:02:44.188
<i> Take me to a hospital, please.</i>

01:02:44.822 --> 01:02:46.454
- [Rook]<i> All right.</i>

01:02:47.461 --> 01:02:49.858
- What do we do?

01:02:49.894 --> 01:02:51.723
- The kid's doing an act.

01:02:52.602 --> 01:02:54.100
Don't you go soft
belly on me now.

01:02:54.736 --> 01:02:56.464
- This is not your
show, you get it?

01:02:57.637 --> 01:02:58.864
Are we clear on that?

01:02:59.467 --> 01:03:01.199
- You're gonna let
these two fuckers out?

01:03:01.234 --> 01:03:02.801
Keep that shit going!

01:03:02.837 --> 01:03:03.738
Now!

01:03:04.141 --> 01:03:06.038
- Our time doubles
with a homicide,

01:03:06.441 --> 01:03:08.146
so we're gonna try
every chance we can.

01:03:10.517 --> 01:03:11.446
Work with me, man.

01:03:14.456 --> 01:03:17.485
(suspenseful music)

01:03:21.594 --> 01:03:23.626
Checkmate, James.

01:03:24.095 --> 01:03:25.730
There's only one
way outta this thing

01:03:25.765 --> 01:03:27.401
where you're still breathing.

01:03:27.803 --> 01:03:32.273
Hey Casey, three seconds
to open up the door.

01:03:32.309 --> 01:03:35.338
(suspenseful music)

01:03:37.773 --> 01:03:38.638
One.

01:03:41.975 --> 01:03:42.851
Two.

01:03:50.060 --> 01:03:51.250
Three!

01:03:51.285 --> 01:03:53.994
Go get the C4 in the van, go on.

01:03:57.292 --> 01:03:59.791
(fire whooshes)
(Tex screams)

01:04:00.567 --> 01:04:03.366
(dramatic music)

01:04:06.237 --> 01:04:10.010
(Tex screams)
(dramatic music continues)

01:04:12.340 --> 01:04:14.850
(taser zapping)
(Smoke groans)

01:04:23.889 --> 01:04:25.686
(gun bangs)
(James groans)

01:04:26.355 --> 01:04:28.490
- [James]<i> Holy fuck.</i>
(fire whooshing)

01:04:29.828 --> 01:04:33.191
(light dramatic music)

01:04:33.226 --> 01:04:34.793
- [Casey] Come on!

01:04:37.570 --> 01:04:39.468
(gun bangs)

01:04:46.850 --> 01:04:50.182
- Don't miss your chance,
'cause it's closing.

01:04:52.322 --> 01:04:53.548
Closing fast.

01:04:58.924 --> 01:05:01.927
Come on, kid, don't be stupid.

01:05:01.963 --> 01:05:03.690
You can still walk
away with your life,

01:05:04.929 --> 01:05:06.264
you just gotta open up.

01:05:08.933 --> 01:05:10.070
- What about my dad?

01:05:12.806 --> 01:05:15.842
- He's already marked his grave,

01:05:15.877 --> 01:05:17.407
don't bring yourself
down with him.

01:05:20.376 --> 01:05:21.948
- You know, I'd
like to trust you,

01:05:21.983 --> 01:05:24.444
but let's face it,
besides everything else,

01:05:24.479 --> 01:05:27.081
you're all really
bad fucking liars.

01:05:27.117 --> 01:05:28.715
- Open the fucking hatch!

01:05:31.928 --> 01:05:34.396
We're gonna get in there
one way or the other,

01:05:34.431 --> 01:05:35.557
that I can promise you.

01:05:43.472 --> 01:05:46.205
(ominous music)

01:05:48.235 --> 01:05:50.869
(Smoke groans)

01:05:53.817 --> 01:05:57.051
- Motherfuckers, you
fucking amateurs!

01:05:59.015 --> 01:06:01.583
(gun banging)

01:06:04.860 --> 01:06:07.253
- Have you lost
your fucking mind!

01:06:07.288 --> 01:06:08.929
- These two are dead!

01:06:08.964 --> 01:06:10.424
- If you keep firing
with that impact blast,

01:06:10.459 --> 01:06:12.297
you're gonna tear
through us first!

01:06:12.332 --> 01:06:15.295
- Yeah, you know, you
really are the motherfucker

01:06:15.330 --> 01:06:17.297
of all jinxes, do you know that?

01:06:17.333 --> 01:06:18.902
Who did the scouting?
- I did,

01:06:18.937 --> 01:06:20.765
you psychotic asshole.

01:06:20.801 --> 01:06:23.308
I'm the only reason you
know about this score!

01:06:23.343 --> 01:06:27.444
- Oh, yeah, and this job
has been a fucking disaster!

01:06:29.517 --> 01:06:30.950
(gun clicks)

01:06:30.985 --> 01:06:32.787
- Ask yourself
what you want more,

01:06:32.822 --> 01:06:35.782
the money or a
bullet in your head.

01:06:38.058 --> 01:06:40.818
- Our demo guy's
all over the bridge,

01:06:40.853 --> 01:06:42.787
our driller's toast
and this little bitch

01:06:42.823 --> 01:06:45.099
won't even let me smoke
these two rent-a-cops.

01:06:50.136 --> 01:06:51.198
You better come
up with something,

01:06:51.233 --> 01:06:53.206
you cocksucking bastard.

01:06:54.335 --> 01:06:56.108
- Is that a threat?

01:06:56.143 --> 01:06:58.379
- How long have we
known each other, huh?

01:06:58.415 --> 01:06:59.311
A dozen years?

01:07:00.980 --> 01:07:02.611
That's not a threat, my friend.

01:07:04.048 --> 01:07:05.218
Call it a forewarning.

01:07:07.457 --> 01:07:10.025
(Echo coughs)

01:07:11.860 --> 01:07:13.457
- You all right?
- Yeah. Yeah.

01:07:15.094 --> 01:07:17.564
- Let's get this
thing over with.

01:07:17.600 --> 01:07:18.528
- This fucking guy.

01:07:20.437 --> 01:07:21.559
- Are you hit?

01:07:21.594 --> 01:07:23.201
- [Casey] I don't think so.

01:07:23.236 --> 01:07:25.571
- Thank god that guy
can't shoot for shit.

01:07:25.606 --> 01:07:27.541
(hand thuds)

01:07:27.577 --> 01:07:28.802
- All good in there?

01:07:35.509 --> 01:07:37.184
Tensions are running high.

01:07:40.714 --> 01:07:42.585
You might say we're
at a stalemate.

01:07:43.524 --> 01:07:44.987
Agreed?

01:07:45.023 --> 01:07:46.160
- What do you want?

01:07:48.421 --> 01:07:49.427
- What do I want?

01:07:50.966 --> 01:07:53.494
If I had guys like
you on my side,

01:07:53.530 --> 01:07:55.928
this job would've
been over hours ago.

01:07:57.597 --> 01:07:59.503
There's only one way out, Casey.

01:08:01.578 --> 01:08:02.836
Don't take too long.

01:08:03.910 --> 01:08:07.214
(light dramatic music)

01:08:10.784 --> 01:08:13.583
(birds chirping)

01:08:25.735 --> 01:08:27.896
- It's getting hotter in here.

01:08:28.498 --> 01:08:31.271
We're gonna be cooking
in another hour.

01:08:37.139 --> 01:08:38.036
Drink it.

01:08:39.108 --> 01:08:40.812
- I'm fine.

01:08:40.847 --> 01:08:42.249
- I'm not asking.

01:08:43.848 --> 01:08:44.746
Come on.

01:08:46.019 --> 01:08:47.884
(light dramatic music continues)

01:08:47.920 --> 01:08:50.719
(water sloshing)

01:08:56.964 --> 01:08:58.991
Do you believe in miracles?

01:09:00.502 --> 01:09:02.269
- No.

01:09:02.304 --> 01:09:05.503
